The infographic was designed as a one-page visual resource to help students understand the importance of digital literacy in everyday academic and personal life. 
It covered key topics such as the meaning of digital literacy, safe internet practices, and maintaining a professional online presence.
The design included simple icons, short definitions, and visually appealing layouts to make the information easy to understand. 
I used color contrast and structured sections to highlight each topic clearly. 
The aim was to make the infographic engaging and informative so that students can quickly grasp essential digital skills.
While creating the infographic, I found it interesting to explore different design elements and how visual representation can improve understanding. However, selecting the right layout and keeping the content concise yet informative was slightly challenging. 
Overall, this task helped me understand the importance of presenting information in a clear and visually effective manner.
